articles.author: Nichola Groom, Cath Turner
articles.description: The angular, polarizing design of the Cybertruck will help boost the Tesla brand, the electric vehicle maker's chief designer said on Thursday, adding that the pickup was no experiment.
articles.title: Cybertruck designer says Tesla stainless steel pickup is no experiment

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Tesla (TSLA.O) is recalling about 120,423 Model S and Model X vehicles in the U.S. over the risk of cabin doors being unlocked during a crash, the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHTSA) said on Friday.
articles.title: Tesla to recall over 120,000 vehicles in US - NHTSA

articles.author: Siyi Liu, Dominique Patton
articles.description: China, the world's top processor of rare earths, on Thursday banned the export of technology to extract and separate the strategic metals, in a further step towards protecting its dominance in several strategic metals.
articles.title: China bans export of rare earth processing tech over national security

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Chinese regulators announced on Friday a wide range of rules aimed at curbing spending and rewards that encourage video games, dealing a blow to the world's biggest games market, which returned to growth this year.
articles.title: China issues rules to curb gaming spend; Tencent, NetEase plunge

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russian President Vladimir Putin on Friday added Russia's biggest car dealership - Rolf - to a list of foreign-owned companies put under the temporary management of the Russian state.
articles.title: Russian state takes temporary ownership of biggest car dealership - decree

articles.author: Steven Scheer
articles.description: Nearly 7,000 miles away in Portland, Oregon, venture capitalist George Djuric said he was compelled to visit Israel during the country's war with Palestinian militant group Hamas and to pledge support for the high-tech sector.
articles.title: US investors see value in Israeli tech firms despite war

articles.author: William Schomberg, Sarah Young
articles.description: Britain's economy might now be in a recession according to data which showed output shrank in the July-to-September period, shortly after finance minister Jeremy Hunt suggested the Bank of England might cut interest rates to help boost growth.
articles.title: UK recession might be under way after economy shrinks in Q3

articles.author: Krishna N. Das
articles.description: India is close to finishing an investigation into a "comprehensive and exhaustive" complaint that a state drug regulator, in return for a bribe, helped switch samples of cough syrups linked to the deaths of children in Gambia before the samples were tested in India, the investigator told Reuters.
articles.title: Exclusive: India probe into bribery claim in toxic syrup tests nears completion

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: More than two dozen Russian drones targeted Ukraine's capital early on Friday, officials said, injuring two people and damaging residential buildings in Moscow's latest overnight drone strike against Ukraine.
articles.title: Mass drone attack hits several Kyiv districts

articles.author: Layli Foroudi
articles.description: Camelia Toldea has packed her family's suitcases ready for a quick exit from an abandoned building where she and dozens of other Roma live, fearful the squat will be next in a wave of evictions near Paris' 2024 Olympic Games facilities.
articles.title: Migrants, Roma evicted from squats ahead of Paris 2024 Olympics
